	<tr>
		
			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				I'm a lvl 32 cleric, and one day I was walkin around Feerrott on my way from Cazic Thule to Rathe Mountains.  Well I'm just mindin my own business exchanging tells with a friend of mine, when all of a sudden I get's an invite into a group.  Well me being the polite, and adventurous priest that I am agrees wwithout asking what the group was huntin.  I guess I shoulda been suspicious when I did a /who and found out that the group leader was lvl 40, but like I said...  I'm adventurous.  Well I asks what were huntin, and it turns out to be spectres.  Well my first reaction was &quot;Hmm how can I get the H%ll  outta this group without looking like a coward&quot; but it was late, and I was bored so I agreed. 30 minutes, and two deaths later I realized that there may have been a slight possiblity that I had made a mistake in agreeing to join this group...  Sure the exp was pretty good, but considering that I lost a bubble from the previous 2 deaths i decided to just leave spectre huntin alone for a while.<BR>
     I thought these guys were moving kinda slow for creatures who so many people seem to be afraid of, but they didn't really need to be up close to kick my butt, they just do a much quicker job.  They attacked faster than anything I'd ever been up close to and hit for I think like 90, but I was paying more attention to trying to zone than to how much HP I was loosing.  I casted panic the dead on one that was following me, but he didn't run, and I didn't see nothing about him resisting it so I guess he just kills things when he's scared.  <BR>
     That's pretty much all I ever had to do with spectres.  They seemed to have kinda a strange aggro going on.  It's hard to explain so I wont bother.  <BR>
<BR>
   A Friendly little Priest of Life on the Mithaniel Marr server<BR>

				</font>
			</td>

