			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				Any cleric or paladin should be able to solo these by kiting them.  They move slow, that is one advantage.  The other one is that your Undead Fear line of spells work on these guys.  Panic the Dead works well, sends them fleeing along at a slow rate.  A pally would then follow along behind, chopping them up and nuking as ordered.  A cleric would follow at a distance, nuking with undead spells.  A swarm of them are nasty, as their lifetap spell when cast on you times four is painful.  Add a few swipes for 80 dmg with those wicked scythes, and you are gonna be in a world of hurt.  Had this happen to my lvl 44 shaman in oasis, got trained by four at once.  I had magic resist buff up so I was left at half hps, and ran off, woulda flat out killed any other caster I believe, or perhaps me if MR was not up.  <BR>
<BR>
Landragoran Heronwing<BR>
Barbarian shaman of the 46th winter<BR>
Lanys<BR>

